Class CodeConstructor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.okorochkova.implementor.CodeConstructor
public class CodeConstructor extends Object
The class constructs the class and its methods, parse it in the String type.

  • Constructor Details

    • CodeConstructor

      public CodeConstructor(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Construct code for the class and write it in String type to code, also write the string result in unicode to codeInUnicode.
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory, where need to implement the class.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when token is not interface or token is private.

  • Method Details

    • writeCodeInFile

      public void writeCodeInFile() throws ImplerException
      Writing the unicode result from codeInUnicode to pathToFile.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when cannot write the result in file.
